 original study will be of interest to scholars and general readers interested in social movements, diaspora studies, empire and African history, publishing history, literary history, and cultural studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican diaspora. 0aAuthors, BlackzGreat BritainxPolitical and social views. 0aBlack peoplexPolitical activityzGreat Britain. 0aBlack peoplezGreat BritainxPolitics and government. 0aDecolonizationzAfricaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPan-AfricanismxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitics and culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aProhibited bookszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPublishers and publishingxPolitical aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aWest IndiansxPolitical activityzGreat Britain. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  aAfrican nationalism.  aAfrican speech.  aBritish rule.  aC. L. R. James.  aConvention People's Party.  aFrench political control.  aGeorge Padmore.  aGold Coast.  aI. T. A. Wallace Johnson.  aInternational African Service Bureau.  aJomo Kenyatta.  aLeopold Senghor.  aPrinting.  aRas Makonnen.  aanti-colonial campaign.  acultured progressives.  alabour-powered nationalism.  aliberation.  aself-government.1 aPolsgrove, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611851640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526118516423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526118516/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles